The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Thursday, May 27, 2004 				 IAF to lost pilots rescue
																								New Delhi, May 26: A woman learning to pilot an aircraft was saved by the Indian Air Force after she lost her bearings in mid-air and nearly ran out of fuel, reports our special correspondent.N.R. Veda, a trainee with the Andhra Pradesh Flying Club in Hyderabad, had taken off from Nadirgul airstrip in her Cessna 152 on Monday morning. 																								Squadron Leader A.K. Yadav, flying an IAF Avro aircraft on a routine training exercise, heard her on the radio frantically seeking help. 																								He abandoned his mission and with his crew traced her. Once she was spotted, the Avro radioed her to follow it. Veda landed safely at Nadirgul just as the Cessna was on it last drops of fuel. 
